<h2>1. Source data and interpretation of the trial design</h2>
<p>BriaCell reported on 12 May 2026 that more than 315 patients had been screened and more than 230 patients had been enrolled in the Bria-ABC Phase 3 study. The same source language frames the pivotal comparison as Bria-IMT plus a checkpoint inhibitor versus physician's choice/TPC, with an interim analysis after <strong>144 patient events - deaths</strong> and overall survival as the primary endpoint.</p>
<p>The ClinicalTrials.gov record describes the study as Bria-IMT regimen plus checkpoint inhibitor/retifanlimab versus treatment of patients'/physicians' choice. Because the monotherapy arm is discontinued after the first 150 patients, the base model excludes the approximately 50 Bria-IMT monotherapy patients from the 144-event main analysis set. This is the interpretation most consistent with public source language; however, because the full statistical analysis plan is not public, an all-randomized sensitivity analysis should be retained as a robustness layer.</p>

